history.content:
Hi all,

I've gotten a number of questions about CS 186's exam plans for next semester. I thought I'd post here to clear some questions up.

I'm aware that our lecture (MW 6:30-8 PM) and final time (F 3-6 PM) conflicts with CS 189's. Lectures will be webcasted, as stated in the course guide. We are currently planning on offering one alternate final timeslot, which is tentatively scheduled for Friday 7-10 PM (right after our main final). This will be the only alternate final we will be offering for the course (barring DSP exceptions, which we work out with the DSP office on an individual basis). Exams for the course will be held in-person, matching the course offering style.

I hope this helps with schedule planning.
history.subject: CS 186 Spring 2022: Alternate Final Exam
